---
// Terms & Conditions for istefox.dev and the Agentwake app. English text, Italian legal
// framework (governing law and consumer rules). Facts sourced from the repo: pricing ladder
// in src/data/pricing.ts, beta program in src/data/agentwake-waitlist.ts and
// functions/api/waitlist.ts, refund and support policy in src/data/agentwake.ts (FAQ).
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const LAST_UPDATED = '23 July 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`Terms & Conditions — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="Terms and conditions for the istefox.dev website and the Agentwake app: licenses, purchases through Polar, refunds, and the beta program."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="legal">
			<h1>Terms &amp; Conditions</h1>
			<p class="updated">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>

			<h2>1. Who operates this site</h2>
			<p>
				istefox.dev and the Agentwake app are operated by Stefano Ferri, an independent software
				developer based in Italy ("I", "me"). You can reach me at
				<a href="mailto:stefferri@icloud.com">stefferri@icloud.com</a>. By using this site or
				Agentwake you accept these terms. If you do not accept them, do not use the site or the
				app.
			</p>

			<h2>2. Scope</h2>
			<p>
				These terms cover the istefox.dev website (including the blog and project pages) and the
				Agentwake macOS application, in both its free and paid (Pro) tiers, including the beta
				program described in section 6. How I handle personal data is described separately in the
				<a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>3. Agentwake: Free and Pro</h2>
			<p>
				Agentwake is distributed as a signed and notarized DMG for macOS 14 or later. The free
				tier (including the keyboard-cleaning lock and live agent status) requires no payment and
				no account. The Pro tier is unlocked by a license key and adds the features listed on the
				<a href="/agentwake">product page</a>.
			</p>
			<p>
				A Pro license is a personal, non-exclusive, non-transferable right to use Agentwake Pro on
				Macs you own or control. It is a one-time purchase: no subscription, and all updates are
				included for the life of the product. You may not resell, sublicense, or share your
				license key, and you may not reverse engineer the app except where the law expressly
				permits it.
			</p>

			<h2>4. Purchases</h2>
			<p>
				Polar Software Inc. ("Polar") processes all purchases as merchant of record. This means
				your sales contract for the payment itself is with Polar: Polar handles the checkout,
				payment processing, invoicing, and applicable taxes, and emails you the license key.
				Polar's own terms and privacy policy apply to the checkout. I remain responsible for the
				app itself and for these terms.
			</p>
			<p>
				Pricing: Agentwake Pro costs €3.99 for the whole of September 2026 and €7.99 from
				1 October 2026 onward. Prices are stated in euro, taxes handled by Polar at checkout. A
				price never moves back down once it has risen, and every date is published in advance on
				the product page.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Refunds</h2>
			<p>
				If Pro is not for you, write to
				<a href="mailto:stefferri@icloud.com">stefferri@icloud.com</a> within 14 days of purchase
				and you get a full refund, no questions asked. This sits alongside, and does not limit,
				any mandatory rights you have as a consumer under EU and Italian law.
			</p>

			<h2>6. Beta program</h2>
			<p>
				Until 31 August 2026 you can join the Agentwake beta by signing up with your email on the
				product page. Beta testers receive the current build and a free lifetime copy of Pro,
				activated through a private checkout link delivered by email. The link is personal, works
				once, and the offer is capped at a limited number of redemptions.
			</p>
			<p>
				The purpose of the beta is to gather feedback before the public launch. Beta builds are
				pre-release software: they are stable and have been in development and testing for about
				six months, but features may still change and occasional defects are to be expected.
				Feedback is welcome through
				<a href="https://github.com/istefox/Agentwake-releases/issues/new">GitHub Issues</a> or by
				email; providing feedback is appreciated but never a contractual obligation.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Updates</h2>
			<p>
				Agentwake updates itself through the Sparkle framework: the app checks for a new version,
				verifies its signature, and installs it. Updates are included with both tiers at no extra
				cost. I may add, change, or retire individual features over time; a feature you paid for
				will not be removed from Pro without a functional replacement.
			</p>

			<h2>8. Acceptable use</h2>
			<p>
				You may not use this site or the app to break the law, to probe or disrupt the site's
				infrastructure, or to circumvent the licensing mechanism. Automated bulk scraping of the
				site, beyond normal search-engine and AI-assistant indexing, is not permitted.
