				belong to their respective owners and are used only to identify the products in question.
			</p>

			<h2>10. Warranty and liability</h2>
			<p>
				The free tier and beta builds are provided "as is", without warranty, to the extent the
				law allows. For paid licenses, the legal guarantee of conformity under EU and Italian
				consumer law applies in full. Nothing in these terms excludes or limits liability for
				intent, gross negligence, or any liability that cannot be excluded by law. Beyond that,
				my liability is limited to the amount you paid for the license.
			</p>
			<p>
				One point specific to what Agentwake does: the app is designed fail-safe, so a missed
				signal lets your Mac sleep rather than keeping it awake. Still, you remain responsible
				for supervising long unattended workloads and for your own backups.
			</p>

			<h2>11. Governing law and disputes</h2>
			<p>
				These terms are governed by Italian law. If you are a consumer in the European Union, you
				also keep the protection of the mandatory rules of your country of residence, and you may
				bring disputes before the courts of your own country as EU law provides. For everyone
				else, the competent court is the one of my registered residence in Italy.
			</p>

			<h2>12. Changes to these terms</h2>
			<p>
				I may update these terms as the product and the law evolve. The "last updated" date at
				the top always reflects the current version, and substantive changes to paid features or
				refund rights will be announced on the product page before they take effect. Continued
				use after a change means you accept the updated terms.
			</p>

			<h2>13. Contact</h2>
			<p>
				Questions about these terms:
				<a href="mailto:stefferri@icloud.com">stefferri@icloud.com</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.legal h1 {
		margin-bottom: 0.2em;
	}
	.updated {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-size: 0.95em;
		margin-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.legal h2 {
		margin-top: 1.6em;
		font-size: 1.25em;
	}
</style>
